HEADWORD: Catharist
<hw>Cath"a*rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>catharista</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/ clean, pure.]</ety> <def>One aiming
at or pretending to a greater purity of like than others about him; --
applied to persons of various sects. See <er>Albigenses</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

